headlines.description: — Zach LaVine scored 43 points, including 17 in the fourth quarter, and DeMar DeRozan added 37 as the Sacramento Kings rallied for a 127-117 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Monday to strengthen their bid for a first-round home game in the play-in...
headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine and DeRozan combine for 80 points in Kings 127-117 win over the Pistons

headlines.description: — Duncan Robinson scored 12 of his 21 points in the fourth quarter, Tyler Herro scored 20 and the Miami Heat pulled away to beat the Philadelphia 76ers 117-105 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Robinson scores 21, Herro adds 20 and Heat rally late to beat 76ers 117-105
